// grid container:

A grid container is an element that has the display grid applied; its the direct parent of all the grid items.

// grid items

** direct ** descendants of the grid-container

// gird line

dividing line that make up the structure of the grid; i.e., vertical or horizontal.



// grid track

the space between two adjacent grid lines; like columns of the grid

// grid cell

the space between two adjacent row and two adjacent column grid lines

// grid area

the total space surrounded by four grid lines
